17/01/2006
RUSE, Bulgaria -- A three-day working meeting of representatives from the interior ministries of Bulgaria, Romania and the European Police Office (Europol) began in the Bulgarian city of Ruse on Monday (16 January).
The session is aimed at harmonising the activities of police forces and co-ordinating the fight against organised crime in the two states, which are scheduled to join the EU in January 2007.
(BNR - 16/01/06)
